==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoar
<hw>Hoar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>hor</ets>,
<ets>har</ets>, AS. <ets>h⟦amac⟧r</ets>; akin to Icel.
<ets>h⟦amac⟧rr</ets>, and to OHG. <ets>h⟦emac⟧r</ets> illustrious,
magnificent; cf. Icel. <ets>Hei⟦edh⟧</ets> brightness of the sky, Goth.
<ets>hais</ets> torch, Skr. <ets>k⟦emac⟧tus</ets> light, torch. Cf.
<er>Hoary</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>White, or grayish white; <as>as,
<ex>hoar</ex> frost; <ex>hoar</ex> cliffs</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Hoar</xex> waters.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gray or white with age; hoary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose beard with age is <qex>hoar</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old trees with trunks all <qex>hoar</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Musty; moldy; stale.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoar</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hoar
<hw>Hoar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Hoariness; antiquity.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Covered with the awful <qex>hoar</qex> of innumerable ages.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoar</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hoar
<hw>Hoar</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>h⟦amac⟧rian</ets> to grow
gray.]</ety> <def>To become moldy or musty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

